subSubSection.paragraph:
Male terminalia (
Figs 2a–c, j
, 
3b
). Pygidium with relatively deep punctures, with short pale hair-like setae, and long dense pale setae at apex. Spiculum gastrale bilobed, stout, almost straight (
Fig. 2j
). Median lobe of penis evenly thick (
Figs 2a, b
), with thin margins in ventral view; apex with curved sides tapering to acute point (
Fig. 2c
); length about equal to that of apodemes; moderately thick, with deflected apex in lateral view. Tegmen (
Fig. 3b
) oval, with thicker parameres; manubrium slightly curved.

Female genitalia (
Figs 3e, h
). Spiculum ventrale thin, spatulate (
Fig. 3e
). Spermatheca nearly C-shaped; cornu thickened, narrowing towards apex; ramus and collum swollen, oblique (
Fig. 3h
).
